Types:
i)if
ii)if-else
ii)switch case

->conditional statements are used to check the condition and to print the relevent block in constant time 

->if-pseudo code:
public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int n = 10;
        if(n == 10){
            System.out.println("hi");
        }
    }
}

->if-else Pseudo code:
public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int n = 10;
        if(n == 10){
            System.out.println("hi");
        }else{
            System.out.println("Bye")
        }
    }
}

->switch-case pseudo code:
public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int n = 10;

    }
}
